Munt la Schera Tunnel.label: Munt la Schera Tunnel
Munt la Schera Tunnel.description:
The Munt la Schera Tunnel is a single lane road tunnel located in the Swiss canton of Grisons. It connects the Engadin valley with Lago di Livigno, through Munt la Schera.
The tunnel is now open 24 hours a day. Wikipedia

Sierre Tunnel.label: Sierre Tunnel
Sierre Tunnel.description:
The Sierre Tunnel is a tunnel near Sierre in the Swiss canton of Valais. It is part of the A9 Autobahn and is located between Sierre and Sierre-Est-Ouest.
The tunnel was opened in 1999 and consists of two tubes of 2,460 metres in length. Wikipedia

Callahan Tunnel.label: Callahan Tunnel
Callahan Tunnel.description: The Callahan Tunnel, officially the Lieutenant William F. Callahan Jr. Tunnel is one of three tunnels beneath Boston Harbor in Boston, Massachusetts. Wikipedia

Ted Williams Tunnel.label: Ted Williams Tunnel
Ted Williams Tunnel.description: The Ted Williams Tunnel, also known as the Williams Tunnel, is the name of the third highway tunnel under Boston Harbor in Boston, Massachusetts, the Sumner and Callahan Tunnels being the other two. Wikipedia

Thomas P. O'Neill Jr. Tunnel.label: Thomas P. O'Neill Jr. Tunnel
Thomas P. O'Neill Jr. Tunnel.description: The Thomas P. "Tip" O'Neill, Jr. Tunnel is a highway tunnel built as part of the Big Dig in Boston, Massachusetts. It carries the Central Artery underneath downtown Boston, and is numbered as Interstate 93, U.S. Route 1, and Route 3. Wikipedia

Hvalfjörður Tunnel.label: Hvalfjörður Tunnel
Hvalfjörður Tunnel.description: Hvalfjörður Tunnel is a road tunnel under the Hvalfjörður fjord in Iceland and a part of Route 1. It is 5,770 m long and reaches a depth of 165m below sea level. Wikipedia

Great St Bernard Tunnel.label: Great St Bernard Tunnel
Great St Bernard Tunnel.description: The Great St Bernard Tunnel, Italian Traforo del Gran San Bernardo, German Tunnel des Grossen Sankt Bernhard is a road tunnel complementing the Great St Bernard Pass, linking Martigny with Saint-Rhémy-en-Bosses. Wikipedia

Limehouse Link tunnel.label: Limehouse Link tunnel
Limehouse Link tunnel.description: The Limehouse Link tunnel is a 1.1 mile long tunnel in the Limehouse area of east London on the A1203 road which links the northern approach of Tower Bridge with a point just north of Canary Wharf in London Docklands. Wikipedia

Bjørvika Tunnel.label: Bjørvika Tunnel
Bjørvika Tunnel.description: The Bjørvika Tunnel is a motorway immersed tunnel on European Route E18 in the city center of Oslo, Norway. The tunnel has two bores, with three lanes in each. Wikipedia

Eiksund Tunnel.label: Eiksund Tunnel
Eiksund Tunnel.description: The Eiksund tunnel is an undersea tunnel in Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. The tunnel runs under the Vartdalsfjorden connecting Ørsta Municipality and Ulstein Municipality. Wikipedia

Fort McHenry Tunnel.label: Fort McHenry Tunnel
Fort McHenry Tunnel.description: The Fort McHenry Tunnel is a four-tube, bi-directional tunnel that carries traffic on Interstate 95 underneath the Baltimore Harbor. The lowest point in the Interstate System under water, the tunnel is named for nearby Fort McHenry. Wikipedia

Sumner Tunnel.label: Sumner Tunnel
Sumner Tunnel.description: The Sumner Tunnel is a road tunnel in Boston, Massachusetts, USA. It carries traffic under Boston Harbor in one direction, from Logan International Airport and Route 1A in East Boston. Wikipedia

Jack Lynch Tunnel.label: Jack Lynch Tunnel
Jack Lynch Tunnel.description:
The Jack Lynch Tunnel is an immersed tube tunnel and an integral part of the N40 southern ring road of Cork in Ireland. It is named after former Taoiseach, Jack Lynch, a native of Cork.
It takes the road under the River Lee. Wikipedia

Honningsvåg Tunnel.label: Honningsvåg Tunnel
Honningsvåg Tunnel.description: Honningsvåg Tunnel is a road tunnel on the island of Magerøya in Nordkapp Municipality in Finnmark county, Norway. It is located slightly north of the undersea North Cape Tunnel, and it is part of the European route E69 highway. Wikipedia

2nd Street Tunnel.label: 2nd Street Tunnel
2nd Street Tunnel.description: The 2nd Street Tunnel is a widely filmed and photographed tunnel on 2nd Street under Bunker Hill in Downtown Los Angeles, California. It has been described as "the most recognizable city landmark most Americans have never heard of". Wikipedia

Allegheny Mountain Tunnel.label: Allegheny Mountain Tunnel
Allegheny Mountain Tunnel.description: The Allegheny Mountain Tunnel is a vehicular tunnel carrying the Pennsylvania Turnpike through the Allegheny Mountains. At this point, the Turnpike carries Interstates 70 and 76. Wikipedia

Bømlafjord Tunnel.label: Bømlafjord Tunnel
Bømlafjord Tunnel.description: The Bømlafjord Tunnel is a subsea road tunnel under Bømlafjorden which connects the island of Føyno in Stord to the mainland at Dalshovda in Sveio, Norway. The tunnel is 7.820 kilometers long and reaches 260.4 m below mean sea level. Wikipedia

Blackwall Tunnel.label: Blackwall Tunnel
Blackwall Tunnel.description: The Blackwall Tunnel is a pair of road tunnels underneath the River Thames in east London, England linking the London Borough of Tower Hamlets with the Royal Borough of Greenwich, and part of the A102 road. Wikipedia

Broadway Tunnel (Los Angeles).label: Broadway Tunnel
Broadway Tunnel (Los Angeles).description: The Broadway Tunnel was a tunnel under Fort Moore Hill in Los Angeles, California, downtown, extending North Broadway, at Sand Street, one block north of Temple Street, northeast to the intersection of Bellevue Avenue, to Buena Vista Street. Wikipedia

Broadway Tunnel (San Francisco).label: Broadway Tunnel
Broadway Tunnel (San Francisco).description: The Broadway Tunnel is a roadway tunnel in San Francisco, California. The tunnel opened in 1952, and serves as a high-capacity conduit for traffic between Chinatown and North Beach to the east and Russian Hill and Van Ness to the west. Wikipedia

Burnley Tunnel.label: Burnley Tunnel
Burnley Tunnel.description: The Burnley Tunnel is a tollway tunnel in Melbourne, in Victoria, Australia, which carries traffic eastbound from the West Gate Freeway to the Monash Freeway. It is part of the CityLink Tollway operated by Transurban. Wikipedia

Byfjord Tunnel.label: Byfjord Tunnel
Byfjord Tunnel.description: The Byfjord Tunnel is a subsea road tunnel which runs between the mainland at Randaberg and Sokn in Rennesøy, Norway. The tunnel is 5,875 meters long and opened in 1992 as a toll road. It is part of European Road 39 and the Rennesøy Fixed Link. Wikipedia

Caldecott Tunnel.label: Caldecott Tunnel
Caldecott Tunnel.description: The Caldecott Tunnel is a four-bore highway tunnel through the Berkeley Hills between Oakland, California and Orinda, California. Wikipedia

Carlin Tunnel.label: Carlin Tunnel
Carlin Tunnel.description: The Carlin Tunnel is a collective name for a set of four tunnel bores east of Carlin, in Elko County, Nevada, USA. Each of the four bores was constructed for a different purpose and at a different time. Wikipedia

Cave Rock Tunnel.label: Cave Rock Tunnel
Cave Rock Tunnel.description: The Cave Rock Tunnel is a dual bore highway tunnel on U.S. Route 50 along the eastern shore of Lake Tahoe approximately seven miles north of Stateline, in Douglas County, Nevada, USA. Wikipedia

Domain Tunnel.label: Domain Tunnel
Domain Tunnel.description: The Domain Tunnel is a road tunnel located in Melbourne, Australia, which carries traffic westbound from the Monash Freeway to the West Gate Freeway, running under the Yarra River and Kings Domain. Wikipedia

Eisenhower Tunnel.label: Eisenhower Tunnel
Eisenhower Tunnel.description: The Eisenhower Tunnel, officially the Eisenhower–Johnson Memorial Tunnel, is a dual-bore, four-lane vehicular tunnel approximately 50 mi west of Denver, Colorado, United States. Wikipedia

Festning Tunnel.label: Festning Tunnel
Festning Tunnel.description: The Festning Tunnel is a motorway tunnel on European Route E18 in the city center of Oslo, Norway. The tunnel has two tubes, with three lanes in each. It runs from Bjørvika, under Akershus Fortress, The City Hall Square and Vika to Filipstad. Wikipedia

Frøya Tunnel.label: Frøya Tunnel
Frøya Tunnel.description: The Frøya Tunnel is an undersea tunnel connecting the municipalities of Frøya and Hitra in Sør-Trøndelag county, Norway. The tunnel is located about 4 kilometres south of Sistranda on Frøya. Wikipedia

Gaviota Tunnel.label: Gaviota Tunnel
Gaviota Tunnel.description: The Gaviota Tunnel is a tunnel on U.S. Route 101 completed in 1953 in the center of Gaviota State Park, 33 miles northwest of Santa Barbara, California. It is 420 feet long and 17.5 feet tall. Wikipedia

George Massey Tunnel.label: George Massey Tunnel
George Massey Tunnel.description: The George Massey Tunnel is a highway traffic tunnel in the Metro Vancouver region of southwestern British Columbia. Wikipedia
Owner: British Columbia Toll Highways and Bridge Authority

Halsnøy Tunnel.label: Halsnøy Tunnel
Halsnøy Tunnel.description: The Halsnøy Tunnel is a subsea road tunnel which connects the island of Halsnøy to the mainland at Sunde in Kvinnherad, Norway. The tunnel is 4,120 meters long and reaches 135 meters below mean sea level. Wikipedia

Heroes Tunnel.label: Heroes Tunnel
Heroes Tunnel.description: Heroes Tunnel is a 1,200-foot-long, twin-tube tunnel carrying Route 15 through West Rock Ridge in New Haven, Connecticut. Wikipedia

Hitra Tunnel.label: Hitra Tunnel
Hitra Tunnel.description: The Hitra Tunnel is an undersea tunnel connecting the island municipality of Hitra to the mainland municipality of Snillfjord in Sør-Trøndelag county, Norway. Wikipedia

Hsuehshan Tunnel.label: Hsuehshan Tunnel
Hsuehshan Tunnel.description: The Hsuehshan Tunnel or "Snow Mountain" tunnel, is the longest tunnel in Taiwan, located on the Taipei-Yilan Freeway. It opened on June 16, 2006. Wikipedia

Kingsway Tunnel.label: Kingsway Tunnel
Kingsway Tunnel.description: The Kingsway Tunnel is a road tunnel under the River Mersey in Merseyside, northwest England, and runs between Liverpool and Wallasey. Wikipedia

Knappe Tunnel.label: Knappe Tunnel
Knappe Tunnel.description: The Knappe Tunnel is a four-lane, twin-tube motorway tunnel partially finished, partially under construction in Bergen, Norway. Wikipedia

Lærdal Tunnel.label: Lærdal Tunnel
Lærdal Tunnel.description: Lærdal Tunnel is a 24.51-kilometre long road tunnel connecting Lærdal and Aurland in Sogn og Fjordane, Norway and located approximately 175–200 kilometres north-east of Bergen. Wikipedia

Limerick Tunnel.label: Limerick Tunnel
Limerick Tunnel.description: The Limerick Tunnel is a 675-metre-long, twin-bore road tunnel underneath the River Shannon on the outskirts of Limerick city. The tunnel forms part of the N18 Limerick Southern Ring Road. The tunnel is tolled. Wikipedia

Lyttelton road tunnel.label: Lyttelton road tunnel
Lyttelton road tunnel.description: The Lyttelton road tunnel links the New Zealand city of Christchurch and its seaport, Lyttelton. It opened in 1964 and carries just over 10,000 vehicles/day. Wikipedia

Mount Bolu Tunnel.label: Mount Bolu Tunnel
Mount Bolu Tunnel.description: Mount Bolu Tunnel is a 2.9 km long highway tunnel constructed through the Bolu Mountain in Turkey between Kaynaşlı and Yumrukaya. Wikipedia

Northbrae Tunnel.label: Northbrae Tunnel
Northbrae Tunnel.description:
The Northbrae Tunnel, also referred to as the Solano Avenue Tunnel, was built as a commuter electric railroad tunnel in the northern part of Berkeley, California and was later converted to street use.
In 1910. Wikipedia

Queensway Tunnel.label: Queensway Tunnel
Queensway Tunnel.description: The Queensway Tunnel is a road tunnel under the River Mersey, in the north west of England, between Liverpool and Birkenhead. It is often called the Birkenhead Tunnel, to distinguish it from the Kingsway Tunnel, which serves Wallasey. Wikipedia

Rohtang Tunnel.label: Rohtang Tunnel
Rohtang Tunnel.description: Rohtang Tunnel is a tunnel being built under the Rohtang Pass in the eastern Pir Panjal range of the Himalayas on the Leh-Manali Highway. Wikipedia
Address: Rohtang Tunnel South Portal Approach Rd

Skatestraum Tunnel.label: Skatestraum Tunnel
Skatestraum Tunnel.description: The Skatestraum Tunnel is a subsea road tunnel between the islands of Rugsundøya and Bremangerlandet in Bremanger Municipality in Sogn og Fjordane county, Norway. Wikipedia

St Helena Tunnel.label: St Helena Tunnel
St Helena Tunnel.description: The St Helena Tunnel is a twin-tube road tunnel under St Helena Hill located near the suburb of Ewingsdale, near Byron Bay, New South Wales, Australia. Wikipedia

Sydney Harbour Tunnel.label: Sydney Harbour Tunnel
Sydney Harbour Tunnel.description: The Sydney Harbour Tunnel is a twin-tube road tunnel in Sydney, Australia. The tunnel was completed and opened to traffic in August 1992 to provide a second vehicular crossing of Sydney Harbour to alleviate congestion on the Sydney Harbour Bridge. Wikipedia

Terrace Motorway Tunnel.label: Terrace Motorway Tunnel
Terrace Motorway Tunnel.description: The Terrace Tunnel takes the Wellington Urban Motorway under The Terrace in central Wellington, New Zealand. Opened in 1978, it is 460 metres in length. Wikipedia

Tussen Tunnel.label: Tussen Tunnel
Tussen Tunnel.description: The Tussen Tunnel is a 2,840-meter long road tunnel located on County Road 64 in Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. Wikipedia

Washburn Tunnel.label: Washburn Tunnel
Washburn Tunnel.description: The Washburn Tunnel is a two-lane underwater motor-vehicle tunnel connecting Galena Park and Pasadena, two suburbs of Houston, Texas. Completed in 1950, it travels north-south underneath the Houston Ship Channel. Wikipedia

Waterview Connection.label: Waterview Connection
Waterview Connection.description: The Waterview Connection is a motorway section under construction through west/central Auckland, New Zealand. Wikipedia

Wawona Tunnel.label: Wawona Tunnel
Wawona Tunnel.description: The Wawona Tunnel is a highway tunnel in Yosemite National Park. It, and Tunnel View just beyond its east portal, were completed in 1933. Wikipedia

Genting Sempah Tunnel.label: Genting Sempah tunnel
Genting Sempah Tunnel.description: The Genting Sempah Tunnel is the first highway tunnel in Malaysia. Located on the Kuala Lumpur-Karak Expressway, the 900-metre tunnel connects Hulu Gombak in Selangor to Genting Sempah, Pahang. This tunnel was constructed between 1977 and 1979. Wikipedia

Cadí Tunnel.label: Cadí Tunnel
Cadí Tunnel.description: Cadí Tunnel is a toll road tunnel in Catalonia, Spain, connecting the comarques of Cerdanya and Berguedà. Wikipedia

Brynglas Tunnels.label: Brynglas Tunnels
Brynglas Tunnels.description: The Brynglas Tunnels carry the M4 motorway under Brynglas Hill in Newport, South Wales. The 1,200-foot-long twin-bored tunnels were the first tunnels in the British motorway network and are still the only bored tunnels. Wikipedia

Fløyfjell Tunnel.label: Fløyfjell Tunnel
Fløyfjell Tunnel.description: The Fløyfjell Tunnel is a road tunnel in the city of Bergen, Norway. The tunnel goes through the Fløyfjellet mountain massif between Sandviken and Kalfaret. Wikipedia

Freifjord Tunnel.label: Freifjord Tunnel
Freifjord Tunnel.description: The Freifjord Tunnel is a 5,086-metre long undersea tunnel under the Freifjorden in Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. The tunnel is part of the Norwegian National Road 70. Wikipedia

Ordu Nefise Akçelik Tunnel.label: Ordu Nefise Akçelik Tunnel
Ordu Nefise Akçelik Tunnel.description: Ordu Nefise Akçelik Tunnel, originally Hapan Tunnel, is a highway tunnel constructed in Ordu Province, northern Turkey. With its length of 3,820 m, it is the country's longest tunnel. Wikipedia

Rya Tunnel.label: Rya Tunnel
Rya Tunnel.description: The Rya Tunnel is a subsea road tunnel which links the island of Kvaløya to the Malangshalvøya peninsula. Located along Norwegian County Road 858, the tunnel runs under Straumsfjorden between the villages of Larseng and Balsnes. Wikipedia

Lincoln Tunnel.label: Lincoln Tunnel
Lincoln Tunnel.description: The Lincoln Tunnel is a 1.5-mile-long tunnel under the Hudson River, connecting Weehawken, New Jersey and Midtown Manhattan, New York City, in the USA. Wikipedia

Wuhan Yangtze River Tunnel.label: Wuhan Yangtze River Tunnel
Wuhan Yangtze River Tunnel.description: The Wuhan Yangtze River Tunnel, is the first tunnel under the Yangtze River. Trial operation commenced on December 28, 2008. It takes about 7 minutes to cross the Yangtze River by car using the tunnel. Wikipedia

Strákagöng.label: Strákagöng
Strákagöng.description: Strákagöng is a tunnel in Iceland, located in Norðurland vestra along Route 76. It has a length of 800 m and was opened in 1967. Wikipedia

North Cape Tunnel.label: North Cape Tunnel
North Cape Tunnel.description: North Cape Tunnel is one of the longest subsea road tunnels in Norway. It is located in Nordkapp Municipality in Finnmark county in the far northern part of Norway. Wikipedia

Qingdao Jiaozhou Bay tunnel.label: Qingdao Jiaozhou Bay tunnel
Qingdao Jiaozhou Bay tunnel.description: Qingdao Jiaozhou Bay tunnel is an under-sea road tunnel located in Shandong Province in eastern People's Republic of China. Wikipedia

Almannaskarðsgöng.label: Almannaskarðsgöng
Almannaskarðsgöng.description: Almannaskarðsgöng is a tunnel along Route 1, located near Höfn in Austurland in eastern Iceland. The tunnel measures exactly 1312 metres in length and was opened on June 24, 2005. Wikipedia

Bolungarvíkurgöng.label: Bolungarvíkurgöng
Bolungarvíkurgöng.description: Bolungarvíkurgöng is a tunnel in northwestern Iceland, located in Vestfirðir along Route 61. It has a length of 5,156 m and opened on September 25, 2010. Wikipedia

Figueroa Street Tunnels.label: Figueroa Street Tunnels
Figueroa Street Tunnels.description: The Figueroa Street Tunnels are a set of four four-lane tunnels that carry northbound traffic on State Route 110 through Elysian Park in Los Angeles, California, United States. Wikipedia
